description: The Florida Supreme Court ruled to uphold a 15-week ban on abortion in the state, while allowing a proposed amendment that would enshrine abortion protections in the state constitution to appear on the November ballot.
title: Florida Supreme Court allows 6-week abortion ban to take effect, but voters will have the final say

description: Google agreed to destroy billions of data records to settle a lawsuit claiming it secretly tracked the internet use of people who thought they were browsing privately.
title: Google to destroy browsing data to settle consumer privacy lawsuit

description: Nine students won this year's national handwriting contest. A growing number of states are requiring cursive instruction, and research supports the benefits of writing on paper.
title: Winners of national penmanship contest crowned as handwriting is 'having a moment'

description: Dallas police are reportedly looking to speak with Kansas City Chiefs wide receiver Rashee Rice after two luxury cars were involved in a high-speed crash and the occupants of the vehicles walked away from the scene.
title: Kansas City Chiefs player Rashee Rice reportedly sought after multi-vehicle crash caused by speeding luxury cars

description: Swara Salih, a 32-year-old Kurdish American, has been reluctantly ticking “white” on federal forms his whole life.
title: Not 'white,' not 'other': Middle Eastern and North African communities finally get counted

description: With the massive salvage operation underway at the collapsed Baltimore Key bridge, officials are now planning to create a temporary channel that will allow commercial ships to access the critical port. NBC’s Aaron Gilchrist reports for TODAY.
title: Demolition crews begin cutting into Baltimore bridge wreckage

description: Powerful storms are on the move after a rough weekend out west. Tens of millions from Texas to New England are in the path of heavy rain, damaging winds and possible tornadoes. NBC’s Jesse Kirsch reports and TODAY’s Al Roker tracks the latest forecast.
title: Major storms expected in much of US threatening snow, floods
